western Tehran FIR, a major airspace region, with only limited, approved exceptions, satisfying the rule's definition of a broad, non‑weather closure.\"}`.\n\nMake sure to not include extra spaces? It's fine.\n\nNow we need to execute that tool call. Then after that, presumably the tool will return `ok:true`. Then we must report that vote was accepted and stop. But the instructions: \"After `aar_submit_council_vote` returns `ok: true`, report that your vote was accepted and stop. Do not call `aar_wait_for_opportunity` again after your vote is accepted.\" So we need to make the tool call, wait for a response, then respond to the user that the vote was accepted.\n\nThus next step is to make tool call. Let's do that.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6592998c528c478799879a53","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-nano-30b-a3b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782830158831,"responseId":"gen-1782830159-tJ9bjL6RFbhUHOjy1pj1"}}
